Whereas implementation of the European Energy Charter is of fundamental importance to Europe's  future, allowing the Commonwealth of Independent States and the countries of central and eastern  Europe to develop their energy potential, while helping to improve security of supply;
Whereas it is necessary to consolidate the initiative and the central role of the Community, to  enable the latter to participate fully in the implementation of the Treaty;
